The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 May is 42,198 (4,884.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 May, there were 48 new confirmed cases (5.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 May, there were 65 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 26% (17 fewer cases).
